That's a low blow. That will happen.

43
00:04:13,171 --> 00:04:14,251
- Will it?
- It will happen.

44
00:04:14,297 --> 00:04:15,841
Shit, my violin!

45
00:04:17,342 --> 00:04:19,153
- Help me, please. I don't know why.
- What is going on?

46
00:04:19,177 --> 00:04:20,262
I'm suddenly 6 years old.

47
00:04:20,929 --> 00:04:24,349
Oh, God. All right. Why the tie, hmm?

48
00:04:25,142 --> 00:04:26,393
Not another funeral?

49
00:04:27,269 --> 00:04:29,146
- It's The Turd's idea.
- Oh.

50
00:04:29,229 --> 00:04:32,524
And no, no. Not all my patients die, anyway.

51
00:04:34,401 --> 00:04:36,486
Why are you so dressed up?
What's his name?

52
00:04:37,028 --> 00:04:39,573
Ladies' tea. Planning the fundraiser.

53
00:04:39,656 --> 00:04:42,617
Oh, the school auction.
Did I mention I'm not going?

54
00:04:42,701 --> 00:04:45,495
- Oh, did I mention you are?
- I think you'll find I'm not, my love.

55
00:04:45,579 --> 00:04:47,873
Isn't it enough
we give them tons of money?

56
00:04:47,956 --> 00:04:49,183
We actually don't give them money.

57
00:04:49,207 --> 00:04:51,168
- Your dad does, which is sweet of him.
- Uh-huh.

58
00:04:51,585 --> 00:04:53,670
Reminds me, we have dinner with him
next Thursday.

59
00:04:53,753 --> 00:04:56,256
Right. So, I have Reardon
and your dad in the same week.

60
00:04:56,339 --> 00:04:59,676
I'm just the luckiest girl in New York.

61
00:04:59,759 --> 00:05:00,927
Don't you like Reardon?

62
00:05:01,386 --> 00:05:03,388
Well, do you like Reardon?
You like your school?

63
00:05:03,472 --> 00:05:04,473
- Yeah.
- Hey.

64
00:05:04,556 --> 00:05:05,849
Then I love it. Kiss your mom.

65
00:05:05,932 --> 00:05:07,225
- We have to go.
- Mom...

66
00:05:07,309 --> 00:05:09,909
- No, I'm not kissing Mom. You do it.
- You need to clean this up.

67
00:05:09,936 --> 00:05:13,398
- I'm not doing this every single morning.
- I know, I want to kiss you. I like this.

68
00:05:13,523 --> 00:05:14,983
Yeah. Right.

69
00:05:15,066 --> 00:05:16,693
- Henry? Henry?
- What?

70
00:05:16,776 --> 00:05:19,696
No more smoothies.
You never, ever clean up...

71
00:05:19,779 --> 00:05:21,591
All right,
here's a question and don't lie.

72
00:05:21,615 --> 00:05:24,576
Did you, in fact,
practice that thing at all this week?

73
00:05:24,659 --> 00:05:25,827
Because I heard nothing.

74
00:05:25,911 --> 00:05:26,995
No, I practiced.

75
00:05:27,078 --> 00:05:28,205
- Really?
- Yeah. I swear.

76
00:05:30,916 --> 00:05:33,043
Do you know,
he doesn't even think I'm any good.

77
00:05:33,126 --> 00:05:34,294
Mr. Rosenbaum.

78
00:05:34,836 --> 00:05:36,338
He actually said that, did he?

79
00:05:36,421 --> 00:05:38,507
No. It's not that he says it.

80
00:05:38,590 --> 00:05:39,758
It just...

81
00:05:39,841 --> 00:05:42,636
He used to say a lot more good stuff.

82
00:05:42,719 --> 00:05:45,555
I mean, sometimes with the looks
he gives me,

83
00:05:45,639 --> 00:05:47,098
like, I think he wants me to quit.

84
00:05:47,182 --> 00:05:50,101
Well, is it possible that,
as your mom might say,

85
00:05:50,185 --> 00:05:52,145
you're actually projecting that sentiment.

86
00:05:52,229 --> 00:05:54,314
Because somewhere deep down,

87
00:05:54,397 --> 00:05:57,984
in the bowels of your teenage psyche,
you actually want to give it up.

88
00:05:58,068 --> 00:05:59,611
I don't want to give up.

89
00:05:59,694 --> 00:06:01,905
- I love violin.
- Okay, well, that's great, then.

90
00:06:01,988 --> 00:06:03,865
You know, Rosenbaum,
he's an unhappy man.

91
00:06:03,949 --> 00:06:05,408
It is never a good idea

92
00:06:05,492 --> 00:06:08,495
to take measure of ourselves
through the eyes of the joyless.

93
00:06:08,578 --> 00:06:10,789
Well, you can be joyless.

94
00:06:13,208 --> 00:06:14,876
- Beg your pardon?
- Yeah.

95
00:06:14,960 --> 00:06:17,462
You can be joyless when you're stressed.

96
00:06:17,546 --> 00:06:18,880
Do I seem stressed a lot?

97
00:06:19,506 --> 00:06:20,506
Some.

98
00:06:20,966 --> 00:06:22,092
Lately.

99
00:06:22,968 --> 00:06:25,345
Ah. Brilliant. Well, now I'm...

100
00:06:25,428 --> 00:06:27,597
Now I'm stressed
about being stressed, so...

101
00:06:27,681 --> 00:06:29,808
- thank you very much.
- You're welcome.

102
00:06:29,891 --> 00:06:32,435
You don't play your violin
for Rosenbaum, anyway.

103
00:06:32,519 --> 00:06:35,397
You owe him your respect
and your hard work, but in the end,

104
00:06:35,480 --> 00:06:37,148
your relationship with song

105
00:06:37,232 --> 00:06:39,526
is between you and your music.

106
00:06:39,609 --> 00:06:41,820
- Got it.
- Great. And you're brilliant, okay?

107
00:06:41,903 --> 00:06:43,071
So, fuck Rosenbaum.

108
00:06:43,154 --> 00:06:44,364
I'm telling Mom you said that.

109
00:06:44,447 --> 00:06:47,492
Take your violin and shove it up
his Rosenbaum cheeks, okay?

110
00:06:47,576 --> 00:06:48,576
Dad...

111
00:07:09,055 --> 00:07:10,724
- Morning.
- Good morning.

112
00:07:12,601 --> 00:07:15,478
Rebecca Harkness has arrived
way too early.

113
00:07:15,562 --> 00:07:17,063
Oh, great.

114
00:07:17,647 --> 00:07:20,191
- It doesn't make any sense to me.
- Huh.

115
00:07:20,275 --> 00:07:22,569
One minute, he's attentive, loving.

116
00:07:22,652 --> 00:07:25,405
The next minute he's borderline abusive.

117
00:07:25,488 --> 00:07:29,034
I got both swings last night.
The full pendulum.

118
00:07:29,117 --> 00:07:32,912
And fucking forbid I call him bipolar.

119
00:07:32,996 --> 00:07:35,915
I mean, fucking forbid!

120
00:07:35,999 --> 00:07:39,794
So, you're back to thinking
that he's, um... That he's bipolar.

121
00:07:39,878 --> 00:07:41,921
I don't know. The mood swings...

122
00:07:43,131 --> 00:07:44,131
What do you think?

123
00:07:46,092 --> 00:07:47,344
Well, I don't know him.

124
00:07:48,428 --> 00:07:50,347
- I only know you.
- Meaning?

125
00:07:54,392 --> 00:07:57,687
- Do not give me that look.
- This is your third marriage. Isn't it?

126
00:07:57,771 --> 00:07:59,773
So, what, we're keeping score?

127
00:07:59,856 --> 00:08:01,441
No. No, I'm just...

128
00:08:02,609 --> 00:08:03,735
I'm not doing that.

129
00:08:03,818 --> 00:08:06,279
Okay, this is going somewhere,
and I'm not exactly sure where,

130
00:08:06,363 --> 00:08:08,948
other than a direction not in my favor.
So, just say it.

131
00:08:10,950 --> 00:08:13,244
- Say it! I pay you. Say it.
- Re...

132
00:08:14,204 --> 00:08:15,246
Rebecca.

133
00:08:18,208 --> 00:08:21,836
I have met few people
more discriminating than you.

134
00:08:22,420 --> 00:08:26,216
You read 100 Yelp reviews before choosing
someone to install your carpet.

135
00:08:26,299 --> 00:08:30,845
Am I right? You try on 20 pairs of shoes
before making a choice.

136
00:08:30,929 --> 00:08:33,014
You do background checks
on your hair colorist.

137
00:08:33,098 --> 00:08:34,974
You did a background check on me,
no doubt.

138
00:08:35,058 --> 00:08:37,435
You vet everything. Everything.

139
00:08:37,519 --> 00:08:38,519
Which is fine.

140
00:08:38,561 --> 00:08:40,563
- I mean, that's appropriate.
- But?

141
00:08:40,647 --> 00:08:43,316
But an attractive man comes along...

142
00:08:44,234 --> 00:08:46,861
and shows an interest in you,
and judgment be gone.

143
00:08:46,945 --> 00:08:48,613
That is not what is happening.

144
00:08:48,697 --> 00:08:50,532
I mean, the day that you met Kevin,

145
00:08:50,615 --> 00:08:52,826
you floated into this office.

146
00:08:52,909 --> 00:08:55,704
It was an appointment that was made
to deal with the anguish

147
00:08:55,787 --> 00:08:56,996
of husband number two,

148
00:08:57,080 --> 00:08:59,582
only to declare that you'd met
husband number three.

149
00:09:00,208 --> 00:09:01,251
So, I'm saying...

150
00:09:02,627 --> 00:09:04,379
maybe it's possible...

151
00:09:05,714 --> 00:09:08,842
that you're less of a victim
of Kevin's moods than you are of your own.

152
00:09:08,925 --> 00:09:10,844
So, excuse me, this is my fault?

153
00:09:10,927 --> 00:09:13,513
- No.
- It is. You're blaming me.

154
00:09:13,596 --> 00:09:16,141
I'm not blaming you.
I'm just saying there's a particular

155
00:09:16,224 --> 00:09:17,934
type of person that you want to be with,

156
00:09:18,017 --> 00:09:19,561
and maybe you're a little too quick

157
00:09:19,644 --> 00:09:21,896
to see that person in the men that you meet,

158
00:09:21,980 --> 00:09:24,065
instead of seeing what's actually there.

159
00:09:27,819 --> 00:09:30,363
<i>Oh, well,
I'll probably never see her again</i>

160
00:09:30,447 --> 00:09:33,032
<i>because they hire you
to give them the hard truths,</i>

161
00:09:33,116 --> 00:09:35,618
<i>and then they fire you
for delivering them.</i>

162
00:09:35,702 --> 00:09:37,537
Well, so just up your prices.

163
00:09:37,620 --> 00:09:40,457
The more exclusive you seem,
the more she'll come begging.

164
00:09:40,540 --> 00:09:41,833
Wow.

165
00:09:41,916 --> 00:09:44,377
I have some bad news. The, um...

166
00:09:45,462 --> 00:09:49,048
The dress code for the fundraiser
is fancy-glam.

167
00:09:49,132 --> 00:09:50,425
I'm not wearing a tux.

168
00:09:50,508 --> 00:09:52,510
<i>Listen, this is
for Henry's school.</i>

169
00:09:52,594 --> 00:09:56,931
If I can tough out a ladies' tea,
you can stomach one fundraiser.

170
00:09:57,015 --> 00:09:57,973
For Henry.

171
00:09:57,974 --> 00:10:00,478
I will do it.
But not for Henry's school.

172
00:10:00,560 --> 00:10:01,853
I will do it for you.

173
00:10:02,687 --> 00:10:03,687
Because you're hot.

174
00:10:04,189 --> 00:10:06,566
Anyway, I'm here. Okay?

175
00:10:06,649 --> 00:10:08,568
Later, smart-ass.

176
00:10:08,651 --> 00:10:09,819
Yeah, later. Bye.

177
00:10:15,950 --> 00:10:17,285
- Come in.
- Hi.

178
00:10:18,620 --> 00:10:21,080
- Let me take your coat.
- Yes.

179
00:10:22,749 --> 00:10:24,375
They're waiting for you upstairs.

180
00:10:27,378 --> 00:10:28,379
Hello!

181
00:10:28,463 --> 00:10:30,215
- Sorry I'm late.
- Not a problem.

182
00:10:31,549 --> 00:10:34,135
- We have a new mom. A scholarship.
- Oh.

183
00:10:35,178 --> 00:10:37,282
She brought her infant.
She's changing her in the bathroom.

184
00:10:37,305 --> 00:10:38,848
You look fabulous.

185
00:10:38,932 --> 00:10:40,451
- Oh, hi, Grace.
- Hi.

186
00:10:40,475 --> 00:10:42,060
Is she, uh, on the committee?

187
00:10:42,143 --> 00:10:43,978
Wants to be an involved parent.

188
00:10:44,062 --> 00:10:45,855
Hi. Hi, hi. Sorry.

189
00:10:46,523 --> 00:10:48,149
- Hey.
- Thanks.

190
00:10:48,233 --> 00:10:50,276
Did any of you even know
that she was coming?

191
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:52,570
I mean, I'm usually the first one
to learn of anything.

192
00:10:52,654 --> 00:10:54,113
People can't wait to tell me stuff.

193
00:10:54,197 --> 00:10:56,366
Because you're so quick
to disapprove.

194
00:10:56,449 --> 00:10:57,951
Well, exactly.

195
00:10:58,785 --> 00:11:00,763
- We should get going here.
- Sorry.

196
00:11:00,787 --> 00:11:05,041
Somebody's a bit nervous.
She's back to being the auctioneer.

197
00:11:05,124 --> 00:11:07,853
- You got the guy from Sotheby's.
- No, he dropped out.

198
00:11:07,877 --> 00:11:10,380
- We'll be fine. I've done this before.
- Hi.

199
00:11:10,463 --> 00:11:11,965
Hi. Hi.

200
00:11:12,048 --> 00:11:13,925
I'm Grace Fraser.

201
00:11:14,008 --> 00:11:16,177
Elena Alves. Nice to meet you.

202
00:11:16,261 --> 00:11:18,137
- Hi.
- Elena has a boy in fourth grade.

203
00:11:18,221 --> 00:11:19,889
You said his name was Miguel?

204
00:11:19,973 --> 00:11:22,559
- Yeah, yeah.
- Your baby's gorgeous.

205
00:11:22,642 --> 00:11:24,269
- Thank you.
- Hello. Boy or girl?

206
00:11:24,352 --> 00:11:25,728
Girl. Teresa.

207
00:11:25,812 --> 00:11:27,272
Oh. Teresa.

208
00:11:27,355 --> 00:11:29,607
- I love your eyelashes.
- Okay, come on, folks.

209
00:11:29,691 --> 00:11:30,942
The auction's tomorrow.

210
00:11:31,025 --> 00:11:32,777
Thank you so much for letting me join.

211
00:11:32,861 --> 00:11:35,905
Are you kidding?
We're happy to get all the help we can.

212
00:11:35,989 --> 00:11:38,533
That you even have the time with two kids.

213
00:11:38,616 --> 00:11:40,535
I have twins, so regret it.

214
00:11:40,618 --> 00:11:41,703
Jolene!

215
00:11:43,371 --> 00:11:44,914
I mean, they're so much work, right?

216
00:11:45,665 --> 00:11:48,793
Okay, let's, uh...
Let's rank the items.

217
00:11:48,877 --> 00:11:50,712
- Yes.
- We'll start with the least expensive.

218
00:11:50,795 --> 00:11:54,007
Work our way up to the... The big tickets.

219
00:11:54,090 --> 00:11:55,717
There's a lot of stuff here.

220
00:11:55,800 --> 00:11:58,928
Well, we have over 200 people
confirmed coming, that's a record.

221
00:11:59,012 --> 00:12:01,598
Thanks to the Spensers lending us
their home.

222
00:12:01,681 --> 00:12:03,558
I did a walk-through yesterday.
Oh, my God.

223
00:12:03,641 --> 00:12:04,893
Did you see the David Hockneys?

224
00:12:04,976 --> 00:12:06,769
Two, on facing walls in the dining room.

225
00:12:06,853 --> 00:12:09,606
- And what about Suki's closet?
- Oh, I'll get there.

226
00:12:09,689 --> 00:12:11,107
Maybe Monday night, with any luck.

227
00:12:11,190 --> 00:12:12,191
Yes!

228
00:12:12,275 --> 00:12:14,068
Okay, let's do this.

229
00:12:14,152 --> 00:12:17,697
Okay, we got four separate stays
in the Hamptons.

230
00:12:17,780 --> 00:12:20,074
A pair in Vale and Aspen.

231
00:12:20,158 --> 00:12:22,410
A cooking lesson at Tribeca for eight.

232
00:12:22,493 --> 00:12:23,995
You never know how much those go for.

233
00:12:24,078 --> 00:12:26,718
Stem-cell face-lift.
Does anybody really believe in those?

234
00:12:26,789 --> 00:12:29,459
Kathy Sennot got one.
Did not work.

235
00:12:29,542 --> 00:12:31,085
We have a bunch of consults.

236
00:12:31,169 --> 00:12:33,606
A college admissions counselor.
A pre-school admissions counselor.

237
00:12:33,630 --> 00:12:36,341
A genealogist that'll come to your house.
That could actually go.

238
00:12:36,424 --> 00:12:38,927
I don't see any artists.
Where are the artists?

239
00:12:39,010 --> 00:12:41,405
Are you saying
we can't scratch up one lousy playwright

240
00:12:41,429 --> 00:12:42,972
in all of New York City?

241
00:12:43,056 --> 00:12:45,475
Grace, maybe you could donate
a therapy session.

242
00:12:45,558 --> 00:12:47,560
I am not doing that. That is not happening.

243
00:12:47,644 --> 00:12:50,146
Why not? "Do I hear $500
on saving your marriage?"

244
00:12:50,229 --> 00:12:52,649
